WEBVTT

00:00.354 --> 00:02.640
Life for women can be difficult.

00:03.021 --> 00:07.612
For mothers in the Central African Republic, it's a daily struggle for survival.

00:08.073 --> 00:16.754
Imagine navigating motherhood while facing violence, forced marriage and barriers to education for yourself and for your children.

00:16.962 --> 00:19.647
This is the reality of living in extreme poverty.

00:19.947 --> 00:27.480
With your support, tier fund can help women learn to read and write so they can earn a living and send their children to school.

00:27.861 --> 00:34.332
We're determined to end extreme poverty and injustice following Jesus' where the need is greatest.

00:34.352 --> 00:35.835
Do you have a heart to help?

00:36.396 --> 00:40.082
Find out more at tierfund.org slash premiere.

00:41.250 --> 00:44.815
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:45.275 --> 00:50.662
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:50.682 --> 00:58.833
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:58.953 --> 01:08.466
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

01:09.730 --> 01:15.340
The dream of Pilate's wife, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part 3.

01:17.003 --> 01:30.205
When he was sat down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him, saying, Have nothing to do with that just man, for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

01:31.507 --> 01:35.314
Matthew's Gospel, chapter 27, verse 19.

01:36.706 --> 01:41.571
Thus, I argue that providence is always co-working with the grace of God.

01:42.753 --> 01:52.503
A great writer who knows but little about divine things, yet nevertheless, tells us he perceives a power in the world which works for righteousness.

01:53.244 --> 01:54.245
Exactly so.

01:55.166 --> 01:56.247
It is well-spoken.

01:56.768 --> 01:59.290
For this is the chief of all powers.

02:00.652 --> 02:06.258
When you and I go out to warn men and women of sin, we are not alone.

02:06.722 --> 02:09.066
All providence is at our back.

02:10.128 --> 02:14.876
When we preach Christ crucified, we are workers together with God.

02:15.938 --> 02:18.963
God is working with us, as well as by us.

02:20.205 --> 02:29.100
Everything that happens is driving towards the end for which we work, when we seek to convince men of sin and of righteousness.

02:30.662 --> 02:32.786
Where the Spirit of God is,

02:33.442 --> 02:36.625
All the forces of nature and providence are mustered.

02:38.126 --> 02:52.420
The fall of empires, the death of despots, the uprise of nations, the making or breaking of treaties, terrific wars and blighting famines are all working out the grand end.

02:53.581 --> 02:53.902
Yay!

02:54.903 --> 03:02.770
And domestic matters, such as the death of children, the sickness of wives, the loss of work,

03:03.362 --> 03:11.210
the poverty of the family, and a thousand other things are working, working, ever working for the improvement of men.

03:12.311 --> 03:20.700
And you and I, lending our poor feebleness to cooperate with God, are marching with all the forces of the universe.

03:22.181 --> 03:23.983
Have comfort then in this?

03:25.144 --> 03:30.770
A worker's for Jesus, suffering many things for him, be of good courage,

03:31.522 --> 03:40.296
for the stars in their courses fight for the servants of the living God and the stones of the field are in league with you.

03:41.638 --> 03:47.968
Secondly, I gather from this story the accessibility of conscience to God.

03:48.930 --> 03:50.792
How are we to reach Pilate?

03:52.014 --> 03:53.958
How are we to give Him warning?

03:55.079 --> 03:59.346
He has rejected the voice of Jesus and the sight of Jesus

04:00.418 --> 04:03.962
Could not Peter be fetched to expostulate with him?

04:05.324 --> 04:08.288
Alas, he has denied his master.

04:09.730 --> 04:11.792
Could not John be brought in?

04:13.174 --> 04:15.757
Even he has forsaken the Lord.

04:17.299 --> 04:19.001
Where shall a messenger be found?

04:20.223 --> 04:21.825
Shall it be found in a dream?

04:22.926 --> 04:27.211
God can get at people's hearts, however hardened they may be.

04:28.333 --> 04:29.234
Never give them up.

04:29.666 --> 04:31.888
never despair of arousing them.

04:32.869 --> 04:42.940
If my ministry, your ministry, and the ministry of the Blessed Book should all seem to be nothing, God can reach the conscience by a dream.

04:44.241 --> 04:56.274
If the sword cometh not at them at close quarters, yet what seems but a stray arrow from a bow drawn at a venture shall find out the joints in their harness.

04:57.250 --> 05:05.037
We ought to believe in God about wicked men and never say of them it is impossible that they should be converted.

05:06.559 --> 05:13.826
The Lord can wound Leviathan, for his weapons are many, and they are suited to the foe.

05:15.507 --> 05:26.738
I do not think a dream would operate on my mind to convince me, but certain minds lie open in that direction, and to them a dream may be a power.

05:27.842 --> 05:33.368
God may use even superstition to accomplish his beneficent purposes.

05:34.769 --> 05:38.393
Many, besides Pilate, have been warned by dreams.

05:40.094 --> 05:44.299
Better still, Pilate was accessible through the dream of his wife.

05:45.480 --> 05:55.410
Henry Melville has a very wonderful discourse upon this topic, in which he tries to show that probably, if Pilate had dreamed this dream himself,

05:55.906 --> 06:00.450
It would not have been so operative upon him as when his wife dreamed it.

06:01.291 --> 06:05.195
He takes it as a supposition which nobody can deny.

06:05.995 --> 06:11.741
That pilot had an affectionate and tender wife who was very dear to him.

06:12.642 --> 06:17.466
The one brief narrative which we have of her certainly looks that way.

06:18.427 --> 06:25.714
It is evident that she loved her husband dearly and would therefore prevent his acting unjustly to Jesus.

06:26.370 --> 06:31.677
to send a warning by her was to reach Pilate's conscience through his affections.

06:32.899 --> 06:40.128
If his beloved wife was distressed, it would be sure to weigh heavily with him, for he would not have her troubled.

06:40.909 --> 06:47.658
He would feign shield his tender one from every breath of wind and give her perfect comfort.

06:48.299 --> 06:51.564
And when she pleads, it is his delight to yield.

06:52.465 --> 06:56.370
It is therefore no small trouble to him that she is suffering.

06:56.930 --> 07:08.788
suffering so much as to send a message to him, suffering because of one who deserves her good opinion, one whom he himself knows to be without fault.

07:09.910 --> 07:26.034
If this lady was indeed the wife of Pilate's youth, tender and dearly beloved, and if she was gradually sickening before his eyes, her pale face would rise before his loving memory, and her words would have bound us power over him.

07:26.338 --> 07:30.543
when she said, I have suffered many things in a dream.

07:31.264 --> 07:33.988
O cloudier, popular, if that were thy name.

07:34.809 --> 07:43.439
Well did the Lord of Mercy entrust his message to thy persuasive lips, for from thee it would come with tenfold influence.

07:44.461 --> 07:53.152
Tradition declares this lady to have been a Christian, and the Greek church have placed her in their calendar as a saint.

07:53.172 --> 07:54.994
For this we have no evidence

07:55.458 --> 08:03.669
All that we know is that she was Pilate's wife and used her wifely influence to stay him from this crime.

08:05.352 --> 08:13.403
How often has a tender, suffering, loving woman exercised great power over a coarse, rough man?

08:13.443 --> 08:22.195
The all wise one knows this, and hence he often speaks to sinful men by this influential agency.

08:23.217 --> 08:24.178
He converts

08:24.354 --> 08:28.498
one in a family, that she may be his missionary to the rest.

08:29.920 --> 08:38.389
Thus he speaks with something better than the tongues of men and of angels, for he uses love itself to be his orator.

08:39.711 --> 08:42.714
Affection has more might than eloquence.

08:43.995 --> 08:51.383
That is why, my friend, God sent you for a little while, that dear child who prattled to you about the Savior.

08:52.384 --> 08:54.066
She has gone to heaven now,

08:54.946 --> 09:03.980
but the music of her little hymns rings in your ear even now, and her talk about Jesus and the angels is yet with you.

09:05.342 --> 09:15.098
She has been called home, but God sent her to you for a season to charm you to Himself and win you to the right way.

09:16.019 --> 09:23.090
Thus, He bade you cease from sin and turn to Christ, and that dear Mother of yours,

09:23.330 --> 09:24.952
who is now before the throne.

09:25.633 --> 09:29.178
Do you remember what she said to you when she was dying?

09:30.059 --> 09:37.228
You have heard me a great many times, but you never heard a sermon from me like that address from her dying couch.

09:38.150 --> 09:42.375
You can never quite forget it, or shape yourself free from its power.

09:43.577 --> 09:45.419
Beware how you trifle with it.

09:46.801 --> 09:50.706
To pilot, his wife's message was God's ultimatum.

09:51.842 --> 09:56.808
He warned him never again, and even Jesus stood silent before him.

09:58.349 --> 10:13.306
Oh, my friend, to you it may be that your child, your mother, or your affectionate wife may be God's last messenger, the final effort of the warning angel to bring you to a better mind.

10:14.587 --> 10:20.434
A loving relative pleading with tears is often the forlorn hope of mercy.

10:22.082 --> 10:31.536
An attack so skillfully planned and wisely conducted may be regarded as the last assault of love upon a stubborn spirit.

10:33.058 --> 10:36.964
And after this, it will be left to its own devices.

10:38.526 --> 10:49.042
The selection of the wife was no doubt made by infinite wisdom and tenderness, that if possible, Pilate might be arrested in his career of crime.

10:49.506 --> 10:56.436
and strengthened to the performance of an act of justice by which he would have avoided the most terrible of crimes.

10:57.918 --> 11:04.929
So then we may safely conclude that the Lord has his missionaries where the city missionary cannot enter.

11:05.610 --> 11:11.138
He sends the little children to sing and pray where the preacher has never heard.

11:12.760 --> 11:19.410
He moves the godly woman to proclaim the gospel by her lip and life where the Bible is not read.

11:20.162 --> 11:29.376
He sends a sweet girl to grow up and win a brother or a father, where no other voice would be allowed to tell of Jesus and his love.

11:30.638 --> 11:32.321
We thank God it is so.

11:33.122 --> 11:36.748
It gives hope for the households of this godless city.

11:37.689 --> 11:42.837
It gives us hope, even for those for whom the Sabbath bell rings out in vain.

11:44.140 --> 11:44.921
They will hear.

11:45.502 --> 11:48.306
They must hear these home preachers.

11:48.642 --> 11:51.206
these messengers who tug at their hearts.

11:53.029 --> 12:09.214
I, and let me add that where God does not employ a dream, nor use a wife, yet he can get at men's conscience by no visible means but by thoughts which come unbidden and abide upon the soul.

12:10.656 --> 12:17.266
Truths long buried suddenly rise up, and when the person is in the very act of sin,

12:17.698 --> 12:22.343
they are stopped in the way as Balam was when the angel met him.

12:23.405 --> 12:28.831
How often it has happened that conscience has met a guilty man.

12:30.032 --> 12:39.784
Even in the moment when he meant to enjoy the pleasure bought with wrong, even as Elijah met Ahab at the gate of Naboth's vineyard.

12:41.366 --> 12:45.010
How the king starts back as he beholds the prophet.

12:45.474 --> 12:48.838
he would sooner have seen the very fiend than Elijah.

12:50.220 --> 12:54.946
Angrily, he cries, hast thou found me, O mine enemy?

12:56.548 --> 13:00.873
Though indeed, Elijah was his best friend, had he known it.

13:02.395 --> 13:11.807
Often does conscience pounce upon a man when the sweet morsel of sin has just been rolled under his tongue, and he is sitting down to enjoy it.

13:12.808 --> 13:14.610
The visitation of conscience

13:14.978 --> 13:21.125
turns the stolen honey into bitterness, and the forbidden joy into anguish.

13:22.987 --> 13:33.938
Conscience often lies like a lion in a thicket, and when the sinner comes along the broad road, it leaps upon him, and for a while he is sorely put to it.

13:35.560 --> 13:44.850
The bad man is comparable to Leviathan, of whom we read that his scales are his pride, shut up together as with a close seal.

13:45.602 --> 13:54.457
so that the sword of him that layeth at him cannot hold, the spear, the dart, nor the javelin.

13:54.477 --> 13:58.303
And yet the Lord hath a way of coming at him and of sore wounding him.

13:59.626 --> 14:04.354
Let us therefore both hope and pray for the very worst of men.

14:06.077 --> 14:11.666
Brothers and sisters, use for the good of humanity anything which comes in your way.

14:12.578 --> 14:24.755
Use not only sober argument and sound doctrine, but even if a dream has touched your heart, do not hesitate to repeat it where it may have effect.

14:24.775 --> 14:33.246
Any weapon may be used in this war, but see to it that you do seek the souls of men, all of you.

14:34.288 --> 14:39.014
You who are wives should be especially stirred up to this sacred work.

14:40.076 --> 14:41.618
Remember Pilate's wife,

14:41.922 --> 14:48.752
and think of her as affectionately giving the warning to her husband and go and do likewise.

14:49.974 --> 14:56.704
Never keep back from an ungodly husband the word which may convert him from the error of his ways.

14:57.946 --> 15:02.994
And you, dear children, use sisters, you of the gentler sort.

15:03.755 --> 15:10.866
Do not hesitate in your own quiet way to be heralds for Jesus, wherever your lot is cast.

15:12.002 --> 15:20.232
As for us all, let us take care that we use every occasion for repressing sin and creating holiness.

15:21.594 --> 15:30.085
Let us warn the ungodly at once, for perhaps the man to whom we are sent has not yet performed the fatal deed.

15:30.906 --> 15:34.911
Let us stand in the gap while yet there is space for repentance.

15:36.173 --> 15:40.498
Pilot is even now sitting on the judgment seat.

15:41.154 --> 15:42.515
Time is precious.

15:43.997 --> 15:44.677
Make haste.

15:45.618 --> 15:49.182
Make haste, yet he commits the deed of blood.

15:50.203 --> 15:51.644
Send the messenger to him.

15:52.445 --> 15:54.367
Stop him, air the deed is done.

15:55.228 --> 15:58.151
Even though he should complain of your interference.

15:58.751 --> 16:02.815
Say to him, have nothing to do with this just person.

16:03.576 --> 16:06.238
For I have suffered many things because of him.

16:07.159 --> 16:10.002
And I pray thee, do nothing against him.

16:11.618 --> 16:13.059
That is our second point.

16:13.680 --> 16:14.401
God bless it.

16:15.222 --> 16:21.628
Although I cannot preach upon it as I would, the Spirit of God can put power into it.

16:24.371 --> 16:25.652
Thank you for listening, friends.

16:25.932 --> 16:31.278
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

16:31.298 --> 16:39.346
For more Christian podcasts, sermons and music, head back to the website premier.plus and sign in for free.

16:45.698 --> 16:47.100
Leprosy still exists.

16:47.521 --> 16:50.345
Every two minutes, someone is diagnosed with this disease.

16:50.785 --> 16:53.710
In an unjust world, their suffering won't make the headlines.

16:54.251 --> 16:56.153
It's hidden in the world's poorest places.

16:56.534 --> 16:58.377
The physical effects are devastating.

16:58.697 --> 17:00.760
But the hardest part is how you are treated.

17:01.221 --> 17:07.330
Even if you've been cured, you can be rejected by your family and community, isolated, shamed and forgotten.

17:07.670 --> 17:09.493
But God sees and so do we.

17:09.834 --> 17:11.236
It's time to end Leprosy.

17:11.456 --> 17:15.602
To learn more, visit leprosymission.org.uk slash premiere.

